#. type: YAML Front Matter: title
#: _versions/main/guides/native-transport-reference.adoc
msgid "Native Transport Reference"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/native-transport-reference.adoc
msgid ""
"Quarkus supports Netty's native transports to improve I/O performance on specific platforms.\n"
"This guide explains how to configure and use native transports in your Quarkus application."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =
#: _versions/main/guides/native-transport-reference.adoc
msgid "What are native transports?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/native-transport-reference.adoc
msgid ""
"By default, Quarkus uses Java NIO for network I/O, which works across all platforms but relies on the JVM's abstraction layer.\n"
"Netty provides native transports that bypass this abstraction and directly use platform-specific system calls:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/native-transport-reference.adoc
msgid "**epoll** — Linux-specific transport using the epoll API"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/native-transport-reference.adoc
msgid "**kqueue** — macOS/BSD transport using the kqueue API"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/native-transport-reference.adoc
msgid "**io_uring** — Linux-specific transport using the io_uring API"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/native-transport-reference.adoc
msgid "Native transports can provide:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/native-transport-reference.adoc
msgid "Lower latency for I/O operations"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/native-transport-reference.adoc
msgid "Reduced CPU overhead"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/native-transport-reference.adoc
msgid "Better scalability under high connection counts"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/native-transport-reference.adoc
msgid "Access to platform-specific socket options"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/native-transport-reference.adoc
msgid ""
"The performance benefit varies by workload.\n"
"Applications with high I/O volume or many concurrent connections typically see the most improvement."
msgstr ""

