#. type: Title ==
#: _versions/main/guides/native-transport-reference.adoc
msgid "Profile-based configuration"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/native-transport-reference.adoc
msgid ""
"Since native transport properties are fixed at build time, you can use Quarkus profiles to configure different transports per environment.\n"
"This is useful when developing on macOS and deploying on Linux:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/native-transport-reference.adoc
msgid ""
"The `%dev` profile applies during `quarkus dev`, while `%prod` applies when building production artifacts.\n"
"This lets you develop locally without native transport dependencies and enforce them in production."
msgstr ""

