msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/native-transport-reference.adoc
msgid ""
"Even when a transport dependency is on the classpath, the native library may fail to load at runtime (e.g., running on a different platform, or the kernel does not support io_uring).\n"
"Quarkus checks the actual transport status at startup:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: _versions/main/guides/native-transport-reference.adoc
msgid "When `native-transport=if-available`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/native-transport-reference.adoc
msgid "If the transport fails to load, Quarkus logs a warning and falls back to Java NIO."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: _versions/main/guides/native-transport-reference.adoc
msgid "When `native-transport=required`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/native-transport-reference.adoc
msgid "If the transport fails to load, the application fails to start with an `IllegalStateException`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: _versions/main/guides/native-transport-reference.adoc
msgid "Transport type mismatch"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/native-transport-reference.adoc
msgid "If you request a specific transport type (e.g., `epoll`) but a different transport loaded (e.g., `io_uring`), the application logs a warning or fails depending on the `native-transport` setting."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =
#: _versions/main/guides/native-transport-reference.adoc
msgid "Platform-specific socket options"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/native-transport-reference.adoc
msgid "Native transports provide access to platform-specific socket options not available with Java NIO."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: _versions/main/guides/native-transport-reference.adoc
msgid "Linux (epoll and io_uring)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: _versions/main/guides/native-transport-reference.adoc
msgid "SO_REUSEPORT"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/native-transport-reference.adoc
msgid ""
"Allows multiple sockets to bind to the same address and port.\n"
"The kernel distributes incoming connections across the sockets, improving scalability."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: _versions/main/guides/native-transport-reference.adoc
msgid "TCP_QUICKACK"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/native-transport-reference.adoc
msgid "Disables delayed ACKs, reducing latency for request-response protocols."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: _versions/main/guides/native-transport-reference.adoc
msgid "TCP_CORK"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/native-transport-reference.adoc
msgid "Buffers small packets until the buffer is full or the cork is removed, reducing the number of packets sent."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: _versions/main/guides/native-transport-reference.adoc
msgid "TCP_FASTOPEN"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/native-transport-reference.adoc
msgid "Enables TCP Fast Open, allowing data to be sent in the SYN packet during connection establishment."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: _versions/main/guides/native-transport-reference.adoc
msgid "TCP_USER_TIMEOUT"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/native-transport-reference.adoc
msgid "Sets the maximum time (in milliseconds) that transmitted data may remain unacknowledged before the connection is forcibly closed."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: _versions/main/guides/native-transport-reference.adoc
msgid "OSX (kqueue)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/native-transport-reference.adoc
msgid "Same functionality as Linux (see above)."
msgstr ""

